				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">10 out of 10 rant, unfortunately i am one of those mages that doesn't want snare or slow and would be pleased to have MS4 (wish they would do MS3 in same way too, would make it much more interesting).
<br />

<br />
A few of your points would be nice such as armor (although i would go for Velious level at 55 and Luclin level at 56, no need for a pet to tank like a warrior does)
<br />

<br />
Root usable items... hmm, some wopuld be nice, but i wouldn't mind them to be charged items.
<br />

<br />
Root on Earth pet is great, specially if you chain pets. Replace it for snare, no thanks, i am no druid.
<br />

<br />
Point 7 is the best of them to be honest except i would not like a change in which pet is a which level. But the changes to firepet are super thoughts. Maybe they can do that for the 50-ish firepets too <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Can't talk about pvp, won't either.
<br />

<br />
The game recuires some skill (all games do) and offer a challenge. This game challenges you to do the best with the tools you have. 
<br />

<br />
[hr]
<br />
Personal note:
<br />
I am level 59 now and won't say i have all knowledge about 60+, but reading rants and facts here on the board have always prepared me very well for my upcoming levels and as such i always felt like an experienced player when i was just getting there (super job on this board mages, keep up the posts).
<br />

<br />
One thing i noticed last week:
<br />
(I have a group with various level 65 players in it, chanter, cleric are 65, tank and ranger 61 and a 64 necro. With these people i play daily)
<br />
In this group it's very seriously noticable when i join cause i can dish out a serious amount of damage in a fight and my 59 airpet seems to be able to stun stuff in PoValor after a resist. Also, the chanter loves my malo line before she slows cause resists are near 0.
<br />

<br />
People complain that we are useless atc, but honestly i have never noticed this. 
<br />
Either i could solo (pretty easily till 55, after that grouping is much more fun and XP), or i have a group in a few minutes (no idea yet on waiting times after 60). 
<br />
I am NEVER useless in a group, either by providing raw DPS, pet stun, offtanking, Mod Rod or debuffs (in PoValor too when pet has Virtue and Cleric keeps her eyes on my pet too). The only spell that is truely useless against the mobs in (ie) PoValor is our damageshield, but i don't really feel i miss it. 
<br />
CotH is disabled in some zones, annoying if you wanna save someone a dangerous trip to your group, but not impossible to work with. 
<br />

<br />
All in all i still enjoy the Magician class and the upcoming changes look like a sweet deal to me, but i sincerely get the feeling that some people on this forum chose the wrong class, judging them by their posts. Maybe it's time to look over your own playing a bit and look around a bit for a class you like playing.
<br />

<br />
Oh well, enough from my banter here, gimme back my 2cp and let me get Jabober out for some fun.<br />_________________<br />In the end everything is okay.
<br />
If it's not okay it's not the end.
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=29332">Oliadar</a>, Level 60 Erudite Arch Mage
