			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I refuse to consider this post a rant, instead, I think it makes a lot of solid points with a bit of flair (10 pieces perhaps, but well under the required 15.)
<br />

<br />
IMHO, nothing should be taken off of the table in class balance discussions. Rytan has already stated how powerful pets will be, and doesn't seem open to changing this. He hasn't directly answered the questions on our defensive abilities, and he said he needs more convincing on solo issues. That's a pretty clear signal of which direction we need to take in these discussions, but I agree with Silverblade, more HP for the pets should be considered. 
<br />

<br />
Let us not forget that one of the reasons that Rytan used to justify the canni nerf was so that he could give us pets with more HP, without having to balance around the mana regen implications. My question would be, where are the pets with more hp?
<br />

<br />
Getting back to the defense, solo, and utility discussion:
<br />

<br />
If the earth pet could reliably cast and land snare, this would be fine for pet chaining. Just back up a few steps when you start casting the new pet. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" /> Having more of our pets be made group friendly would be a great idea. Group friendly usually means raid friendly, unless there is an issue with push, this is a change that would benefit all mages, and could easily be justified from a roleplay perspective as well. Simply change the casting messages around a bit so that the earth underneath Soandso becomes soft and sticky.
<br />

<br />
Summoned pet weapons with varying abilities would also add to our versatility in a variety of solo/group/raid scenarios. 
<br />

<br />
Mages being able to cast root or click on a summoned root item would be a nice boost to our basic defense capability.
<br />

<br />
Getting about half of Silver's list implemented would be a good start, and benefit mages of all playstyles, without dramatically increasing our group DPS, which is about the only part of the game that appears to be properly balanced.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Naladini Dreamfyre</a>
<br />
Arch Mage of 63 Seasons - <a href="http://www.stormhammer.org/forums" target="_blank" class="postlink">Stormhammer</a>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-style: italic">Magician pets are not strong enough to justify our lack of a defensive spell, but they are getting better.</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
