<br />

<br />
I'm not sure there is anything "new" in EQ now, only variations of other classes abilities.
<br />

<br />
To not touch on other classes abilities and yet provide a group benefit and a solo benefit you would need to go to such an extreme that it would never be implemented, thanks to the amount of class blurring that has gone on.
<br />

<br />
Some silly examples:
<br />

<br />
A 400 dmg a hit DS fits into the magely theme, it extends an ability we have had from the start, it would greatly benefit both grp and solo play and is far too overpowered.
<br />

<br />
A pet with 100k hps, no class has that many hps and it would make an awsome off tank in a grp and an amazing solo pet.
<br />

<br />
Ok both examples are extreme but thats the difficulty, unless you use other classes abilities to some extent you have to use extreme methods.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=268634" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Jaladim </a> 
